  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_7' aria-label=\" PNB Housing Finance Limited versus Sh. Manoj Saha & Anr pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('7','2025','2025_7_1041_1052','2025INSC847'); ><font size='4'> <strong>PNB HOUSING FINANCE LIMITED<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>SH. MANOJ SAHA & ANR </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 1041</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 847</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007842025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, JOYMALYA BAGCHI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the High Court erred in directing the appellant to hand back the possession of the secured asset to the 1st respondent; whether the 1st Respondent failed to establish pre-existing tenancy in his favour. Headnotes&dagger; Securitisation and Reconstruction and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 &ndash; s.13(2), (4) &ndash; West Bengal Premises Tenancy Act, 1997 &ndash; 1st Respondent claimed to be a tenant of the secured asset since 1987, through an unregistered tenancy agreement &ndash; Tenancy expired in 1992, however, 1st Respondent<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 15-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 9492/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('7','2025','2025_7_1041_1052','2025INSC847','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div>